cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper deals with game theory, specifically repeated Bayesian games, and provides algorithms and strategies for computing optimal solutions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory). Additionally, the paper involves decision-making and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Computer Science - Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Computer Science - Learning). The paper also involves mathematical programming and linear programming, which could place it in cs.DS (Computer Science - Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Computer Science - Systems and Control).
